===[ File Path: ]===============================================================
* File path means the path of file (image, .js. css, .html ...)

                |-----[ File Path Types: ]----|
                |                             | 
      [ Relative Path ]         |      [ Absolute Path ]
  - Relative Path: points       |  - Absolute path refers to the full location
    to a file relative to the   |    of the file starting from the root.
    current File location.      | 

  # NOTE:=======================================================================
  # - It is recommended to use realtive path. Relative path make you project   |
  # 'easy to move' between env.                                                |
  # - If you move your project folder to another computer or server, relative  |
  #   paths still work.                                                        |
  # ============================================================================

===[ Media: <img> (Single Tag) ]================================================
* - <img> is used to 'embed an image file' in HTML page, Unlike <video>, <audio>
    or <picture>, The <img> tag is 'self-contained' and 'does not use' <source>
    'inside it'. 
  - There are several types of images that works on different browsers. Theses 
    are a set of images that works on famous browser google chromge, firefox,
    edge and opera ...
'.png - .apng - .gif - .jpg - .jpeg - .ico - .cur -.jfif - .pjpeg - .pjp - .svg'

  # NOTE:=======================================================================
  # - DO NOT display a lot of images in the webpage.                           |
  # - The Browser takes too much time to load large images.                    |
  # - Pay attention to the copyrighted images.                                 |
  # ============================================================================
  
  > [ Basic Syntax: ]
      <img src="image_path" alt="description of the image" />

  > [ <img>: attrs ]
      __________________________________________________________________________
      | Attribute          | Description                                       |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `src`              | URL/path to the image file                        |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `alt`              | Text 'alternative' if the image can't be displayed|
      |                    | (important for accessibility and SEO)             |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `width` / `height` | Specifies size (can be in pixels or percentage)   |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      # NOTE:> The above attributes are the most important ones. 
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `loading`          | Can be `lazy` to defer loading until the image    |
      |                    | is visible                                        |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `title`            | Tooltip text when the user hovers over the image  |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `srcset`           | Used for responsive images‚Äîdefines multiple image |
      |                    | files for different screen sizes                  |
      |--------------------|---------------------------------------------------|
      | `sizes`            | Works with `srcset` to define image display size  |
      |____________________|_depending on viewport_____________________________|

# INFO:========================================================================= 
# - When the image size is not defined, It is displayed with the original size |
# - The browser blinks if the image size is not defined.                       | 
# - It is recommended to use CSS for image size instead of HTML attributes.    | 
# ==============================================================================

===[ Media: <video> ... </video> ]==============================================
* - <video>: is used to 'embed a video file' directly into a webpage so users 
  can watch it without needing a separate media player or plugin
  video's types that can be included .mp4, .webm and .ogg.
  - <source>: is used to specify multiple media resources for elements like
  <picture>, <audio>, or <video>, It helps the browser choose the best file to
  load based on factors like format, screen size, or resolution.

  > [ Based Syntax: ]

    <video width="X" height="Y" controls>
      <source src="file_path" type="media/type" />
        ...
    </video>

> [ <video>: attrs ]
    ___________________________________________________________________________
    | Attribute          | Description                                        |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `src`              | Specifies the video file (if `<source>` isn't used)|
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `width`/`height`   | Sets the size of the video player.                 |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `controls`         | Displays video controls (play, pause, volume, etc.)|
    |____________________|____________________________________________________|
    # NOTE: The above attrs are the most important ones. 
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `autoplay`         | Starts playing the video automatically             |
    |                    | (may require `muted`).                             |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `muted`            | Starts the video with no sound. Often used with    |
    |                    | `autoplay`                                         |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `loop`             | Restarts the video automatically when it ends.     |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `poster`           | URL of an image shown before the video plays       |
    |                    | (like a thumbnail).                                |
    |--------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
    | `preload`          | Tells the browser what to preload: `auto`,         |
    |                    | `metadata`, or `none`.                             |
    |____________________|____________________________________________________|

> [ <source>: attrs ]
    ___________________________________________________________________________
    | Attribute        | Description                                          |
    |------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
    | `src` / `srcset` | Path to the media file. Use `src` for video/audio,   |
    |                  | `srcset` for images.                                 |
    |------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
    | `type`           | MIME type like `video/mp4`, `audio/ogg`,             |
    |                  | or `image/webp`.                                     |
    |------------------|------------------------------------------------------|
    | `media`          | (Used in `<picture>`) Media query like CSS, e.g.,    |
    |                  | `(min-width: 600px)`.                                |
    |__________________|______________________________________________________|

# NOTE:========================================================================
# - Video resolution must be taken into consideration but in general 360p     |
#   works on all devices.                                                     |
# =============================================================================
  > Ex:
    <video width="360" height="200" controls>
      <source src="https://www.example.com/video.mp4" type="video/mp4">
      <source src="https://www.example.com/video.ogg" type="video/ogg">
      Your browser does not support the video tag!
    </video>

    - The Browser loads the supported format, That is why we load multiple
      sources.
    - 'Your browser does not support the video tag' this message is displayed
      when the <video> tag is not supported by the browser.

# NOTE:=========================================================================
# - The browser blinks when the video dimenstions are not defined, It renders  | 
#   the HTML page and then load the video. That is way you should define       |
#   video dimensions always.                                                   |
# ==============================================================================

===[ Media: <audio> ...</audio> ]===============================================
* <audio> (paired tag): is used to 'embed audio content' like music, sound,
  effects, or podcasts in web page.  
  - Audio files are: .ogg, .wav, and mp3

  > [ Based Syntax: ]
    <audio controls>
      <source src="audio_path" type="audio/[mpeg/ogg]" /> 
      ...
      Your Browser does not support the audio tag!
    </audio>

    # NOTE:=====================================================================
    # - 'Your browser does not support the audio tag!' this message is         |
    # displayed when the <audio> tag is not supported by the browser.          |
    # ==========================================================================
  
  > [ <audio>: attrs ]
     ___________________________________________________________________________
     | Attribute  | Description                                                |
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `src`      | Path to the audio file (can be omitted if using `<source>`)|
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `controls` | Shows the browser's default audio player                   |
     |            | (play, pause, volume, etc.)                                |
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `autoplay` | Starts playing automatically when the page loads           |
     |            | (must be muted or user-initiated in modern browsers)       |
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `loop`     | Repeats the audio once it ends                             |
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `muted`    | Starts the audio with no sound                             |
     |------------|------------------------------------------------------------|
     | `preload`  | Instructs the browser how much of the audio file to preload|
     |____________|_(`auto`,_`metadata`,_`none`)_______________________________|

  > [ <source>: type attr ]
     ___________________________________________________________________________
     | File Extension | `type` value | Description                             |
     |----------------|--------------|-----------------------------------------|
     | `.mp3`         | `audio/mpeg` | - Most widely supported compressed audio|
     | `.ogg`         | `audio/ogg`  | - Open-source format, good compression  |
     | `.wav`         | `audio/wav`  | - Uncompressed audio, large file size   |
     |________________|______________|_________________________________________|

===[ <iframe>: inline frame ]===================================================
* <iframe> is used to 'embed' a single page inside another, It does not split
  the layout into independent panels <frameset>. (<frame> and <frameset> are
  deprecated)

  > [ Based Syntax: ]
    <iframe src="page_url"> </iframe>

  > [ <iframe>: attributes ]
      __________________________________________________________________________
      | Attribute         | Description                                        |
      |-------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
      | `src`             | - (Required) URL of the page to embed.             |
      | `width`           | - Width of the iframe (in pixels or %).            |
      | `height`          | - Height of the iframe.                            |
      | `title`           | - Text description for accessibility               |
      |                   |   (important for screen readers).                  |
      | `name`            | - Name of the iframe, useful for targeting links   |
      |                   |   (`target="iframe_name"`)                         |
      |-------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
      # NOTE: The above attributes are the most important ones.                                             
      |-------------------|----------------------------------------------------|
      | `allowfullscreen` | - Allows fullscreen mode(commonly used with videos)|
      | `loading`         | - Lazy-loads the iframe (`lazy` or `eager`)        |
      | `referrerpolicy`  | - Controls what referrer info is sent              |
      |                   |   (e.g., `no-referrer`)                            |
      | `sandbox`         | - Enables extra restrictions for security          |
      | `allow`           | - Grants specific permissions                      |
      |___________________|___(e.g., `camera`, `fullscreen`, `geolocation`)____|

  > [ Open link inside <ifrime> ]

    <a href="" target="myiframe">Open Url in Iframe</a>
    <iframe name="myiframe"><iframe>

    # INFO:=====================================================================
    # - Youtube gives the option to embed a video without the need to write any|
    #   code. Select Share, then Embed, copy the iframe code and past it in    |
    #   your web page.                                                         |
    # - If the security policy (X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN or DENY), The page |
    #   won't be embeded the iframe.                                           |
    #   |=> (This is a browser-level security restriction) ‚Äî Firefox (and other|
    #   browsers) respect it to protect against attacks like !!!clickjacking!!!|
    # ==========================================================================
